From b82a642ffe8dd96773230e22bb5ca9a2dff66768 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 9 Jun 2026 19:28:40 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix coaching and volunteer forms to use Web3Forms cleanly
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Move src.js to the bottom of body so forms exist before it runs
  (was throwing 'Cannot read properties of null' in the console)
- Remove the old mailto submit handlers for coachForm and volunteerForm
  that conflicted with the Web3Forms POST flow
- Rewrite src.js:
  * Null-safe wiring for both forms
  * Use the existing success boxes instead of alert()
  * Disable the submit button and show "Sending…" during the request
  * Set a friendly subject and from_name on the Web3Forms payload
  * Show an inline error in the same box on network/API failure
  * Reset the form on success

https://claude.ai/code/session_01CQhaur5bgTcTG5y3ok9zon
